The paper deals with algorithms for finding minimum-weight paths and trees in graphs, which are fundamental problems in computer science. The use of exponential time algorithms and approximation algorithms suggests that the paper belongs to the theoretical computer science sub-categories. The specific techniques used, such as dynamic programming and randomized algorithms, are commonly used in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), computational complexity (cs.CC), and machine learning (cs.LG).
